reviews.review_text: fix I see it is being fixed.  Thanks and sorry to have posted too soon.

Nice Job Kudos to the folks that recorded this up in the balcony of Winterland and also to those who aided in the overall presentation. This is a decent AUD and it gets better as it goes.

This was the most awesome of all the GD shows I attended. Some sloppiness but most songs exhibit fire -- especially Jerry on his souped-up Wolf Guitar. Many of these songs are my alltime favorite versions like PITB, China Rider, China Doll, etc and the PITB Reprise where Jerry lets it all hang out ala Peter Townshend of the Who.

As a result of this show I went on tour with the band for the only time I ever toured with them. I saw all the subsequent shows at Winterland in Dec and then all of the January shows in Calif. Except for some fiery shows in the first part of 1978 (like 4-12-78 Cameron) the Dead never really retained the same fire  and it seemed they just gradually slipped ever so incrementally in enthusiasm. Well, they never really captured it like in this show and numerous others of the 1977 year. 

This ranks as the greatest of all but my Rating reflects the stream quality only.
